area_name: Rock that is Higher than I, The

content.description: Hands undercling bellow graffiti. Stay between the two caves until top out. Don't use high left of undercling to keep grade. Big reach up to 2 finger pocket. Move higher, then choose a cave to top out in.
content.location: In between the two big caves.

content.description: SDS both hands undercling bellow grafiti. Left up high to side pool. Right straight up high to three finger pocket. Left up to sloper pocket or high to crimp on cave edge. Rework feet. Left bumps right for good hold. Pull to sit in cave.
content.location: Starts below furthest left cave. Goes straight up under the right half of the cave.

content.description: SDS on left and right side pulls. Heads straight up. Find the hidden mud jug to help with the top out.
content.location: Farthest left small boulder on The Rock that is Higher Than I

content.description:
Slopey conglomerate cracks. Start right in pocket, left in lowest crack. Finish at top left crack or top out. If topping out, watch out for slippery terrain.

 Possible to tie top rope on tree above.
content.location: Right of 80% Better and behind Jo's Crack.

content.description: Start Left in 2 big pockets, Finish Right in 2 more big pockets. Stay a couple feet below the caves to complete a low traverse across. Right to Left is harder.
content.location: Encompasses almost the entirety of the Rock that is Higher than I

content.description: Recommended right to left, but can be done either way. Begin far right of wall and traverse up to cave bottom then left to corner.
content.location: Located on the first big rock when you begin the creekside trail.

content.description: Nice climb with good jugs and cracks. Finish in cave or top out. Can fix a top rope to the tree above to climb with extra safety.
content.location: Middle of the Rock that is Higher than I

content.description: Largest cliff face near Hurricane Creek Park's parking lot. Located directly behind the "Joelder" boulder.
